# Core Principle

Develop like a senior engineer.

Java is the primary backend stack.

Do not refactor main functionality while adding new features unless explicitly required.

Every new feature must first be evaluated as:
- extension of existing module
- new isolated module
- new microservice

Create a microservice only when there is a strong business, data ownership, lifecycle, scalability, reliability, or security reason.

Do not create microservices for purely technical or cosmetic separation.

If a new feature is confidently independent, isolate it immediately behind clear contracts so it can evolve into a microservice.

Prefer evolutionary architecture over premature distribution.